      "sha256": "a1d875d43e63ffb98f300f3fc266bb63580fb41983f1d8979fa2801ee7906229",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A problem due to Ulam. For example if we begin with $3,5$ then the sequence continues $3,5,7,11,13,17,\\ldots$. It is possible that this sequence is infinite."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "f5e43c750db55bfb12a93d7bf35308dffefa61b49c120d3b7fca52873bd9b463",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Given some initial finite sequence of primes $q_1<\\cdots<q_m$ extend it so that $q_{n+1}$ is the smallest prime of the form $q_n+q_i-1$ for $n\\geq m$. Is there an initial starting sequence so that the resulting sequence is infinite?"
    }
  },
